Kenyan women in the business fraternity converged at the Michael Joseph Centre, Nairobi on Thursday to learn basic corporate skills and personal branding. Among the topics being discussed were public image and appropriate personality traits to adopt when going to meet a client.Those present were Kenya Chamber of Commerce and Industry national vice chairman Laban Onditi, KNCCI Women in Business chairperson Mary Muthoni and guest speakers including Etiquette Xcellent chief executive Eunice Nyala and Dana Courier managing director Nancy Amunga.